ong well-known bearers are the American film stars  Susan Hayward  (  1918–75 ) and  Susan Sarandon  (  b. 1946  as  Susan Tomalin )."]},{"name":"Susanna","meanings":["New Testament form (Luke 8:3) of the Hebrew name <i>Shoshana</i> (from <i>shoshan</i> ‘lily’, which in modern Hebrew also means ‘rose’)."]}]},{"name":"Ardella","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Salvatore, Angelo, Sal, Matteo, Vito, Alfonse, Antonino, Carlo, Gaetano, Giovanni, Giulio, Giuseppe.","Italian (southern): habitational name from a place called Cardella in Sicily."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705205,"age":4,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705206,"age":6,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705207,"age":20,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705208,"age":22,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705210,"age":35,"year":"1600","julianDay":2305448,"title":"The Honourable East India Company","description":"The Honourable East India Company, a British joint-stock company, was established in 1600 for trade in the Indian Ocean region. At its height, the British East India Company had a private army which was twice the size of the British Army, ruled large sections of India, and revenues in the millions.","url":"https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofEngland/The-East-India-Company/","urlTitle":"Historic UK - The East India Company","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705212,"age":55,"year":"1620","julianDay":2312753,"title":"The Pilgrims Board the Mayflower","description":"\"The Pilgrims boarded the Mayflower in search of religious freedom in the New World in September 1620. The Mayflower set sail from Plymouth, England, with 102 passengers, 40 of whom called themselves \"\"Saints.\"\" After two stormy months at sea, the ship reached the New World. Nearly half of the group died during their first winter due to malnutrition and the harsh New England winter.\"","url":"https://www.themayflowersociety.org/the-pilgrims/pilgrim-history","urlTitle":"The Mayflower Society - Pilgrim History","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Susan Ardella Robbins was born in 1565, in Kent, England, her father, Thomas B. Robbins, was 35 and her mother, Ida Ann Stobaugh, was 35. She married William Edgar Maxey in 1579, in Suffolk, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died about 1625, in her hometown, at the age of 61, and was buried in Kent, England."},"et":{"1565–Abt 1625":"1565–umbes 1625","1565–1625":"1565–1625","1565–Male":"1565–Surnud","1580–1650":"1580–1650","1530–Male":"1530–Surnud","1530–1625":"1530–1625","1571":"1571","1580":"1580","11 May 1625":"11. mai 1625","Abt 1625":"umbes 1625","13 October 1563":"13. oktoober 1563","1569":"1569","1579":"1579","1600":"1600","1565":"1565","1620":"1620","1587":"1587","1585":"1585","1530":"1530","1650":"1650","